  "root_text": {
    "sn35.136:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 35.136 ",
    "sn35.136:0.2": "14. Devadahavagga ",
    "sn35.136:0.3": "Paṭhamarūpārāmasutta ",
    "sn35.136:1.1": "“Rūpārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā rūparatā rūpasammuditā. ",
    "sn35.136:1.2": "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
    "sn35.136:1.3": "Saddārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā saddaratā saddasammuditā. ",
    "sn35.136:1.4": "Saddavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
    "sn35.136:1.5": "Gandhārāmā … ",
    "sn35.136:1.6": "rasārāmā … ",
    "sn35.136:1.7": "phoṭṭhabbārāmā … ",
    "sn35.136:1.8": "dhammārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā dhammaratā dhammasammuditā. ",
    "sn35.136:1.9": "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
    "sn35.136:1.10": "Tathāgato ca kho, bhikkhave, arahaṁ sammāsambuddho rūpānaṁ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṁ viditvā na rūpārāmo na rūparato na rūpasammudito. ",
    "sn35.136:1.11": "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati. ",
    "sn35.136:1.12": "Saddānaṁ … ",
    "sn35.136:1.13": "gandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn35.136:1.14": "rasānaṁ … ",
    "sn35.136:1.15": "phoṭṭhabbānaṁ … ",
    "sn35.136:1.16": "dhammānaṁ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṁ viditvā na dhammārāmo, na dhammarato, na dhammasammudito. ",
    "sn35.136:1.17": "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati”. ",
    "sn35.136:1.18": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
    "sn35.136:1.19": "Idaṁ vatvāna sugato athāparaṁ etadavoca satthā: ",
    "sn35.136:2.1": "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā, ",
    "sn35.136:2.2": "phassā dhammā ca kevalā; ",
    "sn35.136:2.3": "Iṭṭhā kantā manāpā ca, ",
    "sn35.136:2.4": "yāvatatthīti vuccati. ",
    "sn35.136:3.1": "Sadevakassa lokassa, ",
    "sn35.136:3.2": "ete vo sukhasammatā; ",
    "sn35.136:3.3": "Yattha cete nirujjhanti, ",
    "sn35.136:3.4": "taṁ tesaṁ dukkhasammataṁ. ",
    "sn35.136:4.1": "Sukhaṁ diṭṭhamariyebhi, ",
    "sn35.136:4.2": "sakkāyassa nirodhanaṁ; ",
    "sn35.136:4.3": "Paccanīkamidaṁ hoti, ",
    "sn35.136:4.4": "sabbalokena passataṁ. ",
    "sn35.136:5.1": "Yaṁ pare sukhato āhu, ",
    "sn35.136:5.2": "tadariyā āhu dukkhato; ",
    "sn35.136:5.3": "Yaṁ pare dukkhato āhu, ",
    "sn35.136:5.4": "tadariyā sukhato vidū. ",
    "sn35.136:6.1": "Passa dhammaṁ durājānaṁ, ",
    "sn35.136:6.2": "sammūḷhettha aviddasu; ",
    "sn35.136:6.3": "Nivutānaṁ tamo hoti, ",
    "sn35.136:6.4": "andhakāro apassataṁ. ",
    "sn35.136:7.1": "Satañca vivaṭaṁ hoti, ",
    "sn35.136:7.2": "āloko passatāmiva; ",
    "sn35.136:7.3": "Santike na vijānanti, ",
    "sn35.136:7.4": "maggā dhammassa akovidā. ",
    "sn35.136:8.1": "Bhavarāgaparetebhi, ",
    "sn35.136:8.2": "bhavarāgānusārībhi; ",
    "sn35.136:8.3": "Māradheyyānupannehi, ",
    "sn35.136:8.4": "nāyaṁ dhammo susambudho. ",
    "sn35.136:9.1": "Ko nu aññatra mariyebhi, ",
    "sn35.136:9.2": "Padaṁ sambuddhumarahati; ",
    "sn35.136:9.3": "Yaṁ padaṁ sammadaññāya, ",
    "sn35.136:9.4": "Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti. ",
    "sn35.136:9.5": "Tatiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn35.136:0.1": "Linked Discourses 35.136 ",
    "sn35.136:0.2": "14. At Devadaha ",
    "sn35.136:0.3": "Liking Sights (1st) ",
    "sn35.136:1.1": "“Mendicants, gods and humans like sights, they love them and enjoy them. ",
    "sn35.136:1.2": "But when sights perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering. ",
    "sn35.136:1.3": "Gods and humans like sounds … ",
    "sn35.136:1.4": "",
    "sn35.136:1.5": "smells … ",
    "sn35.136:1.6": "tastes … ",
    "sn35.136:1.7": "touches … ",
    "sn35.136:1.8": "ideas, they love them and enjoy them. ",
    "sn35.136:1.9": "But when ideas perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering. ",
    "sn35.136:1.10": "The Realized One has truly understood the origin, disappearance, gratification, drawback, and escape of sights, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them. ",
    "sn35.136:1.11": "When sights perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily. ",
    "sn35.136:1.12": "The Realized One has truly understood the origin, disappearance, gratification, drawback, and escape of sounds … ",
    "sn35.136:1.13": "smells … ",
    "sn35.136:1.14": "tastes … ",
    "sn35.136:1.15": "touches … ",
    "sn35.136:1.16": "ideas, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them. ",
    "sn35.136:1.17": "When ideas perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily.” ",
    "sn35.136:1.18": "That is what the Buddha said. ",
    "sn35.136:1.19": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: ",
    "sn35.136:2.1": "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, ",
    "sn35.136:2.2": "touches and ideas, the lot of them—",
    "sn35.136:2.3": "they’re likable, desirable, and pleasurable ",
    "sn35.136:2.4": "as long as you can say that they exist. ",
    "sn35.136:3.1": "For all the world with its gods, ",
    "sn35.136:3.2": "this is what they deem happiness. ",
    "sn35.136:3.3": "And where they cease ",
    "sn35.136:3.4": "is deemed as suffering for them. ",
    "sn35.136:4.1": "The noble ones have seen that happiness ",
    "sn35.136:4.2": "is the cessation of substantial reality. ",
    "sn35.136:4.3": "This insight by those who see ",
    "sn35.136:4.4": "contradicts the whole world. ",
    "sn35.136:5.1": "What others say is happiness ",
    "sn35.136:5.2": "the noble ones say is suffering. ",
    "sn35.136:5.3": "What others say is suffering ",
    "sn35.136:5.4": "the noble ones know as happiness. ",
    "sn35.136:6.1": "See, this teaching is hard to understand, ",
    "sn35.136:6.2": "it confuses the ignorant. ",
    "sn35.136:6.3": "There is darkness for the shrouded; ",
    "sn35.136:6.4": "blackness for those who don’t see. ",
    "sn35.136:7.1": "But the good are open; ",
    "sn35.136:7.2": "like light for those who see. ",
    "sn35.136:7.3": "Though close, they do not understand, ",
    "sn35.136:7.4": "the seekers inexpert in the teaching. ",
    "sn35.136:8.1": "They’re mired in desire for continued existence, ",
    "sn35.136:8.2": "flowing along the stream of lives, ",
    "sn35.136:8.3": "mired in Māra’s dominion: ",
    "sn35.136:8.4": "this teaching isn’t easy for them to understand. ",
    "sn35.136:9.1": "Who, apart from the noble ones, ",
    "sn35.136:9.2": "is qualified to understand this state? ",
    "sn35.136:9.3": "Having rightly understood this state, ",
    "sn35.136:9.4": "the undefiled are fully extinguished.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "sn35.136:0.3": "Paṭhamarūpārāmasutta → sagayhasuttaṁ (bj); agayha (pts1ed) ",
    "sn35.136:4.1": "Sukhaṁ → sukhanti (bj); sukhaṁ ca (sya-all) ",
